 old lever.","Note the setting of the lever span adjuster to make sure it is returned to the same position on installation.","The master cylinder does not need to be removed from the motorcycle for removal of the brake lever.","The push rod and rubber boot will be released when the lever is separated from the master cylinder.","Turn the span adjuster fully clockwise to set the brake lever to maximum span.","Master cylinder","Lever assembly","Span adjuster","Lock nut","Pivot bolt","The ","service tool T3880636"," is required to remove the pivot sleeve for front brake lever.","T3880636 - Kit, Brake Lever Pivot Sleeve","Mandrel","Extractor","Installer piece","Support piece","When removing the brake lever pivot sleeve, always wear overalls, eye, face and hand protection. The brake lever sleeve is hardened and liable to splinter if broken. Debris from broken components could cause injury to eyes, face and any unprotected parts of the body.","Remove the lock nut from the lever pivot bolt.","Remove the lever pivot bolt.","Release the lever from the master cylinder assembly.","The push rod and rubber boot will be released when the lever is separated from the master cylinder.","Note the orientation of brake lever pivot assembly and its spring for installation.","Adjust the span adjuster clockwise fully into the brake lever.","Protect the pivot assembly painted surfaces from damage, using a suitable self-adhesive tape such as masking tape.","Fit the extractor to the mandrel as shown.","Mandrel","Extractor","Position the brake lever assembly inverted, with the brake switch lever facing upwards as shown.","Position the mandrel and extractor to the brake lever and press out the pivot sleeve from the brake lever assembly.","Mandrel","Support piece","Extractor","Front brake lever","Lever pivot assembly","Return spring","Always wear eye, hand and face protection when separating brake lever components. Uncontrolled release of the brake lever components may cause the spring to become detached during dismantling. Flying springs may cause injury to eyes, face and any unprotected parts of the body.","Carefully remove the extractor from the brake lever assembly.","Discard the brake lever pivot sleeve from the support piece.","Note the orientation of the lever pivot assembly for installation.","Note the position of the spring for installation.","Carefully detach the lever pivot assembly and its spring from the lever.","Lever","Spring","Lever pivot assembly","Remove the circlip that retains the span adjuster.","Lever","Detent assembly","Circlip","Span adjuster","Span adjuster pivot","Remove the detent assembly for the span adjuster.","Remove the span adjuster and the span adjuster pivot.","Brake lever","Span adjuster","Span adjuster pivot","Bleed Screw","Remove the cover from the bleed screw. Release the bleed screw and remove from the master cylinder assembly.","Master cylinder","Bleed screw","Cover","Piston and Seals","The hose spigot seal and the paint finish on the master cylinder can be easily damaged.","Do not use sharp tools to remove the seal.","Pull the hose inlet spigot and its seal out of the master cylinder.","Hose inlet spigot","Seal","Master cylinder","Carefully use an applicable tool (long nosed pliers or similar) to remove the piston retaining pin.","Piston retaining pin","Master cylinder","Remove the piston, seals and springs assembly."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType11","views":[],"createdAt":"2024-01-20T13:55:45.303Z","updatedAt":"2024-01-20T13:55:45.303Z","__v":0}